Integrate the intended audience in the original prompt.

Here are examples demonstrating how to apply this principle:

[original]
Describe the function of the heart in the human body.
[improved]
Describe the function of the heart in the human body. Assume your audience is a first-year medical student.

[original]
Write the opening paragraph of a fantasy story.
[improved]
Write the opening paragraph of a middle-grade fantasy story, capturing the attention of a young reader around 11 years old.

